{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Required for keeping chat history alive"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"title":"User Token and JWT","roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"JivoSDK"}]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_user_token","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Setup","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_channel_setup","doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_project_config"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, chat history by default has a temporary nature and gets killed when providing another credentials into "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/startUp(channelID:userToken:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", or by calling ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/shutDown()","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It means, for example, if your client logs-out and then logs-in again, you may see him as entirely new client.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"Even in case he uses the same login credentials, and even in case you provide the same user_token for him into SDK.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep chat history alive between login sessions, you have to generate JWT token and use it as user_token."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Below, we explain how to do that."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"#1: Prepare secret","anchor":"1-Prepare-secret"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"First, you need to create your global "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"},{"text":" which you’ll use for generating JWT tokens.","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Please create it accordingly to RFC 7519, with length of 256 bit."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Then, share this secret with us by sending it to "},{"identifier":"info@jivosite.com","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" from e-mail address of your account’s administrator,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"and tell us your Mobile SDK Channel ID so we can configure our JWT environment for you."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"tip","name":"Tip","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You may found this resource useful to generate, sign, and check JWT tokens: ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","isActive":true}]}]},{"text":"#2: Generate token","level":2,"anchor":"2-Generate-token","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"JWT tokens you will generate for your clients, must be:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unique across your account"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"constant for individual client"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"encrypted using your ","type":"text"},{"code":"secret","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Minimal JWT payload must contain “id” field which acts like a client identifier, so here is example of such JWT payload:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["{","    \"id\": \"egor531@example.com\"","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finally, you should feed your JWT as userToken parameter into:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo\/session","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/startUp(channelID:userToken:)"}]},{"name":"Important","style":"important","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For security reasons, you’d better generate JWT tokens on your back-end,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"rather than doing it directly in the mobile app (because your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"secret"},{"type":"text","text":" might be stolen)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/jivosdk\/common_user_token"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]},{"paths":["\/documentation\/jivosdk\/common_user_token"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK"]]},"references":{"https://jwt.io/":{"identifier":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","url":"https:\/\/jwt.io\/","title":"jwt.io","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"jwt.io","type":"text"}]},"info@jivosite.com":{"identifier":"info@jivosite.com","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{